comments:
in SWT 2.1.1 (all platforms, I assume): java.lang.NullPointerException at 
org.eclipse.swt.custom.TableTreeEditor$2.run(TableTreeEditor.java:100)

This is a very reproducable, and annoying NPE.

final Runnable runnable = new Runnable() {
 public void run() {
  if (TableTreeEditor.this.tableTree.isDisposed() || editor == null) return;
  resize();
  editor.setVisible(true);
 }
};

I haven't tried 3.0, but it looks to be still there (unless you are sure 
editor == null before tableTree = null...):

3.0: 

final Runnable runnable = new Runnable() {
      public void run() {
        if (editor == null || editor.isDisposed()) return;
        if (TableTreeEditor.this.tableTree.isDisposed()) return;
        resize();
        editor.setVisible(true);
      }
    };



This fixes it for me in 2.1.1:

if (TableTreeEditor.this.tableTree == null || 
TableTreeEditor.this.tableTree.isDisposed() || editor == null) return;
